						<div class="postbody"><div class="quotetitle">tokumaru wrote:</div><div class="quotecontent">You can create macros like this in ca65 too.  I do it all the time.</div><br />I'm not familiar with ca65.  Does it allow making macros that don't require a given number of input parameters?  (just to confirm.)  Most assemblers require that every macro invocation use the exact number of parameters specified in the macro definition.  You cannot, for example, invoke a particular macro using three input parameters one time, five the next, and six the time after that.</div>

					
